proc merge[A, B](first: var Table[A, B]; second: Table[A, B]; ignoreDup: bool = true): void
Merge first and second into a single Table[A, B]. Exception will be thrown if there are different values with the same key between the two tables. If ignoreDup is set to false, duplicated keys from the two tables will also throw an exception.   Source Edit

Templates

template `?`[T](cond: bool; p: Conditions[T]): T
Tenary operator for inline if else.

Examples:

var a = true
var b: int = a ? 5 | 10
doAssert b == 5
a = false
b = a ? 9 | 3
doAssert b == 3
  Source Edit 
template `??`[T](x: T; y: T): T

Assign the value on the right hand side when the value on the left hand side is nil.

_Note: types like int, string, bool are never nil

Examples:

type
  TestObj = ref object of RootObj
    x: int

var a: TestObj
var b = TestObj()
b.x = 10
doAssert isNil(a) == true
doAssert isNil(b) == false
doAssert (a ?? b).x == b.x
